                  <msItem>
                     <p> Indenture dated <origDate notBefore="1482-03-04" notAfter="1483-03-21">10 July, 22 Ed. IV</origDate>, by which 
               <persName>sir <forename>Richard</forename> 
                           <surname>Corbett</surname>, kt.</persName>,
               grants to <persName nymRef="Forster">
                           <forename>Richard</forename>
                        </persName> and
               <persName nymRef="Forster">
                           <forename>William</forename>
                        </persName>, sons of 
               <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Forster</surname>
                        </persName> and others his
               manor of <placeName type="manor" key="place_108697">Evelegh</placeName>, with all that belongs to
               it in <placeName type="county" key="place_000067">Shropshire</placeName>, to hold for the term of 60 years from the time of the death
               of <persName nymRef="Hanmer">
                           <forename>Ankareta</forename>
                        </persName> who was the wife of
               <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Hanmer</surname>
                        </persName>, at an annual rent of four marks.
               . </p>
